Package controller

Class CommandUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • controller.CommandUtils
  • public class CommandUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    Adds commands to a delayed input stream, that then communicates with the controller. this allows the controller to ensure that it has full commands.

      • addCommand

        public static boolean addCommand​(java.lang.String command,
                                 DelayedInputStream delayedInputStream)
        Adds the given command to a delayed input stream, that can be used to add commands periodically to a SimpleController and any classes that extend it (which DON'T override the control method.
        Parameters:
        command - the command to input that follows the processCommand format.
        delayedInputStream - the delayed input stream to add the command to.

      • preFormatSellOrBuyDateCommand

        public static java.lang.String preFormatSellOrBuyDateCommand​(boolean buy,
                                                             java.lang.String ticker,
                                                             int amount,
                                                             java.time.LocalDate date)
                                                      throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns a preformatted command for buy or sell. to ensure correct order of arguments are made without. a user typing. (used to be able to integrate any form of input with the readable based inputs)
        Parameters:
        buy - true if this is a buy, false if formating a sell command.
        ticker - the stocks ticker value to buy or sell.
        amount - the amount of shares to buy or sell of the stock.
        date - the date to buy or sell the stock on.
        Returns:
        the formatted buy or sell on date command (based on the SimpleController and its implementations supported command formats).
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the date given is null.
